The paper proposes a new approach to combine Restricted Boltzmann Machines (RBMs) for solving combinatorial optimization problems. RBMs are a type of neural network, and the paper discusses using Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) approaches to find solutions. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
